<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="2162">
Consider a game where there are $n$ children (numbered $1,2,\dots,n$) in a circle. During the game, every other child is removed from the circle until there are no children left. In which order will the children be removed?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line has an integer $n$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print $n$ integers: the removal order.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li> $1 \le n \le 2 \cdot 10^5$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>7</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>2 4 6 1 5 3 7</code>    </div>
